episodes.title: “COVER UP?” Prince Andrew’s Ex-Royal Protection Officers Probed Over Epstein Island Visit
episodes.description:
Talk's Samara Gill investigates the latest reporting on disgraced ex-Prince Andrew after it appeared police had begun investigating former royal protection officers over alleged visits to Epstein Island.

It comes as British police have urged people with information to come forward about claims of human trafficking and sexual assault from the 1990s which appeared in the Epstein files.

Surrey Police said the allegations, set out in a redacted report released by the US Department of Justice in December, allegedly took place in Virginia Water between 1994 and 1996.

The force’s call for witnesses comes after an FBI report from July 2020, which appeared in the files, in which somebody alleged they were drugged at night and driven to “paedophile ring parties” in the mid 1990s.

The same person also claims to have been hit by a dark blue car “driven by Prince Andrew” in which they allegedly suffered injuries to their ribs, hip and leg.

episodes.title: Epstein Survivor: Ex-Prince Andrew Should Face US Congress And British Police
episodes.description:
Ashley Ford  Rubright recounted her experiences with Jeffrey Epstein, detailing how she was coerced into massaging him for $200 at a barbecue restaurant in Palm Beach, Florida, when she was 15. The first encounter escalated into a sexual assault, and the second was even more severe. Despite her initial naivety, she returned, believing Epstein's charm and promises.

episodes.title: “Andrew’s Daughters ARE INVOLVED! No One Believes Me!” | Author Drops Beatrice & Eugenie Bombshell
episodes.description:
Pressure is growing for police to investigate Andrew Mountbatten-Windsor’s links to Jeffrey Epstein after new US files highlighted emails and claims about his contact with the convicted sex offender.

Stephen Parkinson, the Director of Public Prosecutions, said “nobody is above the law” and said he had confidence police would act independently. Thames Valley Police said it is assessing allegations, including claims Andrew shared confidential trade envoy documents with Epstein and that an Epstein associate joined an official overseas trip. Buckingham Palace has said the King is ready to support police if asked.

Kevin O'Sullivan speaks with royal author Andrew Lownie.

episodes.title: "A Very Harrowing Story..." | Jeffrey Epstein Victim Shares Her Story On Meeting Andrew On Island
episodes.description:
Andrew Mountbatten-Windsor’s move from his Windsor mansion to the King’s Sandringham Estate has received a cold reception from some of the locals.

Press photographers and TV crews gathered near the entrance to a driveway to Wood Farm Cottage, where Andrew is reported to be staying temporarily, on Wednesday.

A usually quiet lane in the village of Wolferton, by St Peter church, was parked up with cars and a helicopter hovered overhead.

It is understood the former duke’s new home of nearby Marsh Farm is not yet fully ready but he is expected to move in by the start of April.

Talk's Kevin O'Sullivan is joined by Jeffrey Epstein victim Lisa Phillips.

episodes.title: “My Parents Forced Me To Marry The Cult Leader Age 3” Traumatic Account Of How To Survive A Cult
episodes.description:
Serena Kelley was born into the Children of God in the Philippines in 1983. At three years old, Serena was given to the Supreme Leader David Berg as a child bride by her mother. 

It was in his household that she alleges facing constant mental, physical and sexual abuse and being forced to appear in child pornography videos. 

The group, which was founded in 1968 by Berg, began as a new religious movement focused on spreading the Christian message. 

But, as the decades progressed and the group evolved, it began to attract the attention of the international media with regards to its practices involving children. 

And even after she escaped to the US aged 18 in 2001, it took her years to come to terms with the bottled up trauma from her childhood. 

But in 2017, she began her training to become a Trauma Recovery Specialist, becoming the person she wished she had had when she was looking for help. 

This is her story.
